				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/STUDENT_SPOTLIGHT_KRYSTIAN_KOPEC.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-16777 size-full" src="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/STUDENT_SPOTLIGHT_KRYSTIAN_KOPEC.jpg" alt="" width="1160" height="516" /></a></p>
<p>For our seventh Student Spotlight, we chatted to Krystian Kopec, a bass player whose story with SBL began 18 months ago.</p>
<p>Throughout the year, we’ll be catching up with a diverse set of breaking and established talent to air their thoughts and experiences about bass playing, tunes and music in general from their own vantage point (the only thing that anyone can do, really). Want to join them? If you're studying with SBL and would like to share your experiences, then please don't hesitate to <strong><a href="https://www.scottsbasslessons.com/contact">Contact Us</a></strong> as we'd love to share your story and promote your music to the SBL audience!</p>
<h2>Krystian Kopec - Holly Blue</h2>
<p>“I can pretty much say that I consider Scott my personal teacher and someone who has had a great influence on me as a bass player.” Krystian Kopec couldn’t be more thrilled with his progress as a member of SBL. Holly Blue's latest album, Upbeat, the first recording he’s ever been a part of, is everything that any fan of the Polish electronic trio could possibly want. It encapsulates elements of disco, hook-filled house and ’80s synth pop. “We’ve released two singles from the album,” explains Krystian. “Irresistible and Primitive, which is a cover of a Róisín Murphy song. Both were received better than I expected and we had a nice tour across Poland.”</p>
<p>But life hasn’t always been rosy for Krystian in the Holly Blue camp. Although the core of vocalist Sonia Kopeć and producer Emil Blant has remained constant, Krystian has only recently taken up bass duties. “A friend of mine asked if I wanted to join a project that he was working on,” he tells us. “I had been playing guitar and some piano too, so I was a bit surprised when I heard they were actually looking for a bass player. I told him that I couldn't play the bass and he responded by saying: ‘You’ll learn!’ So that’s what I did.”</p>
<p>This would mark the beginning of a hectic time for Krystian, in which he would go on to become the band’s first choice bassist. “It was quite stressful for me, because there were some upcoming concerts that I was supposed to play and the time was short. I needed to build my technique fast and after the first rehearsal it became clear to me that I needed to be much more disciplined and rhythmically precise. I soon realised that playing in a band and playing alone at my apartment are two very different things! That’s something that Scott really helped me with. I knew that random video lessons on YouTube weren’t enough for me to learn how to play the bass well. But it was thanks to YouTube that I came across scottsbasslessons and that’s when a whole new universe opened up for me.”</p>
<p>Before long, Krystian was ready for his first gig. “After a few months of preparation I started playing with the band. As I became more confident about my playing, I even started composing some material for new songs and the other band members liked it. Upbeat is the first album I’ve ever been involved with and it was like a dream. It’s what I’ve always wanted to do and I am very happy and thankful to Scott and all the people in the SBL team for making it possible.”</p>
<p>Check out Krystian below!</p>
<p><iframe width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/puKzXE6L3oU?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p><iframe width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vhhZdLKGkwo?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
